# World Wide View — Implementation Plan

A next-generation, open-source geospatial intelligence platform combining **Worldview's cinematic CesiumJS 3D globe** with **Worldmonitor's data-rich ingestion engine**, built around a **modular plugin ecosystem**, and designed for both **community self-hosting** and **commercial SaaS deployment**.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **CesiumJS + Google 3D Tiles (Recommended)**: For a "low cost, fast, and efficient" setup that looks like Bilawal's "Worldview" videos, I recommend **CesiumJS with Google Maps Photorealistic 3D Tiles**. 
> - **Cost**: Google Provides a **$200/month free credit**, which covers ~33,000 sessions (each session is 3 hours of 3D globe usage). This is essentially **$0 for small-to-medium volume**.
> - **Efficiency**: CesiumJS is built natively for 3D Tiles and time-dynamic data (CZML), making it the "fastest" path to build the cinematic features you want.
> - **Alternatives**: MapLibre GL JS is "lighter" for standard maps but lacks the high-end 3D terrain/building polish. Deck.gl is better suited for the dashboard overlays (which we can still integrate into Cesium).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope for this bootstrap**: This plan covers **Phase 1 — Foundation/MVP** only. This gets you a working 3D globe app with the plugin architecture, 3 live data layers, a timeline, cinematic camera, and a sidebar intelligence panel. Subsequent phases will be planned after Phase 1 ships.

> [!WARNING]
> **API keys required**: 
> - **Google Maps Tile API Key** (Required for Photorealistic 3D Tiles — Includes $200/mo credit).
> - **OpenSky Network** account (free at [opensky-network.org](https://opensky-network.org)).


