### Core Globe Component

#### [NEW] [GlobeView.tsx](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/globe/GlobeView.tsx)
- CesiumJS `Viewer` inside React using Resium
- WGS84 ellipsoid, terrain, imagery layers
- Request render mode for performance
- Integrates with `TimelineSync` for time-based filtering

#### [NEW] [CameraController.ts](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/globe/CameraController.ts)
- Cinematic fly-to animations with easing (Worldview-style smooth transitions)
- 8 regional presets (Global, Americas, Europe, MENA, Asia, Africa, Oceania, LatAm)
- Orbit mode for idle/attract state
- URL state sync (lat, lon, zoom, heading, pitch)

#### [NEW] [LayerRenderer.ts](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/globe/LayerRenderer.ts)
- Renders plugin data as Cesium entities (points, billboards, polylines, polygons)
- Smart clustering via `EntityCluster`
- Progressive disclosure (detail at higher zoom)
- Color/size coding based on data attributes

#### [NEW] [TimelineSync.ts](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/globe/TimelineSync.ts)
- Bidirectional sync between Cesium clock and UI timeline
- Time window filtering (1h, 6h, 24h, 48h, 7d)
- Playback controls, speed multiplier
- Notifies plugins of current time window

