### Plugin System

The heart of the modular architecture. Every data source implements a standard interface.

#### [NEW] [PluginTypes.ts](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/plugins/PluginTypes.ts)
```typescript
export interface WorldPlugin {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  icon: string;
  category: 'aviation' | 'maritime' | 'conflict' | 'natural-disaster' | 
            'infrastructure' | 'cyber' | 'economic' | 'custom';
  version: string;
  
  initialize(context: PluginContext): Promise<void>;
  destroy(): void;
  fetch(timeRange: TimeRange): Promise<GeoEntity[]>;
  getPollingInterval(): number;
  getLayerConfig(): LayerConfig;
  renderEntity(entity: GeoEntity): CesiumEntityOptions;
  
  // Optional UI hooks
  getSidebarComponent?(): React.ComponentType;
  getDetailComponent?(): React.ComponentType<{ entity: GeoEntity }>;
}
```

#### [NEW] [PluginManager.ts](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/plugins/PluginManager.ts)
- Plugin lifecycle (register, initialize, enable, disable, destroy)
- Routes data from plugins → `LayerRenderer`
- Manages polling per plugin
- Emits events via `DataBus`

#### [NEW] [PluginRegistry.ts](file:///c:/dev/World%20Wide%20View/src/core/plugins/PluginRegistry.ts)
- Static registry of built-in plugins + dynamic registration API

